[
    {
        "content": "<p>For example, if i want to define order on a group using its conditions, i cant use the symbol '&lt;' to express the order of the elements of the group. And i found define a new notation works, but this is not good solution. So how can i use the sign \"&lt;\" under such conditions.   </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">llt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">llt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">infix</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">100</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"&lt;&lt;\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">llt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--llt h u v : Prop</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">--failed to synthesize LT W</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">--use `set_option diagnostics true` to get diagnostic information</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">llt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--llt h u v : Prop</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 467420609,
        "sender_full_name": "Shaojun Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1725428551
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because the instance <code>LT</code> depends on an explicit variable, lean is unable to synthesise <code>LT W</code>, making the syntax <code>&lt;</code> not work.</p>",
        "id": 467478768,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1725443480
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"684366\">Edward van de Meent</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/How.20to.20use.20.22.3C.22.20when.20definition.20using.20some.20other.20proposition/near/467478768\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>because the instance <code>LT</code> depends on an explicit variable, lean is unable to synthesise <code>LT W</code>, making the syntax <code>&lt;</code> not work.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thanks for repley. yeah, that's the reason. So how can i write the definition if i want to use '&lt;'</p>",
        "id": 467522465,
        "sender_full_name": "Shaojun Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1725453781
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i'd assume that <code>LT W</code> exists, and add a hypothesis that <code>(. &lt; .) &lt;-&gt; (e . &lt; e .)</code></p>",
        "id": 467528004,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1725454895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>basically, something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- name the equivalence `e` to avoid confusion, because it is not Prop-typed</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">LT</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- you might want to upgrade this assumption if you want `&lt;` to be transitive, antisymmetric, etc.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- in that case, use `Preorder`, `PartialOrder`, or something even higher in the hierarchy</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- assert/assume that `&lt;` is lifted from `Int`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 467530654,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1725455513
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! This is a good solution, i will try this. (there may be some other questions this way because  this example is more simple. Thank you anyway <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span></p>",
        "id": 467535445,
        "sender_full_name": "Shaojun Zhang",
        "timestamp": 1725456346
    },
